From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ci <ci@local>
Date: Mon, 25 May 2026 18:50:00 +0000
Subject: patches/0064-fman-pcd-log-wording-and-postinstall-budget-verdict.patch

PR14z23: fix two PR14z22 diagnostic-log defects exposed by the 2026-05-25
hardware run, and bake the v1.4 §16 Risk #13 hypothesis-(a) verdict
threshold into the kernel log so the operator does not have to compute
it from raw numbers.

Background
----------

PR14z21 (patch 0062) skipped a bogus 64 KiB MURAM pre-reservation in
fman_pcd_init() by setting pcd->muram_offset = (unsigned long)-EINVAL.
The IS_ERR_VALUE() check on the release path then correctly avoids
fman_muram_free of a never-reserved region.

PR14z22 (patch 0063) instrumented the MURAM gen_pool to localise the
residual -ENOMEM previously observed in fman_pcd_manip_chain_create().

The 2026-05-25 hardware run (kernel 6.18.31-vyos with 0062+0063 applied)
on the LS1046A Mono Gateway DK produced two surprising findings that
this patch addresses:

  Finding 1 (cosmetic but confusing):
    The "ready" line at the bottom of fman_pcd_init() unconditionally
    formats pcd->muram_offset as a hex pointer:

      fsl-fman 1a00000.fman: fman_pcd: ready (64 KiB MURAM reserved at \
                              offset 0xffffffffffffffea)

    On the SKIP path (which is now the default since 0062), the offset
    is the -EINVAL sentinel (0xffff...ea), and "64 KiB reserved" is
    actively misleading - no 64 KiB has been reserved.  An operator
    reading dmesg sees an apparent reservation at a clearly-bogus
    address and reasonably concludes the PCD subsystem is broken when
    in fact it is correctly skipping a reservation that should never
    have existed.  Fix the message to reflect the SKIP path explicitly.

  Finding 2 (operationally important):
    The CP-postinstall accounting line from 0063 prints raw "size=%zu B
    avail=%zu B" numbers and leaves the (a) / (b) / (c) verdict
    computation to the operator.  After 0062 unblocked the Path A
    boot-time install (claimed=5 declined=0 failed=0), the gen_pool
    avail dropped to 70400 B out of 393216 B (~17.9%, well below the
    ~80 KiB threshold from 0063's verdict logic).  Bake the verdict
    threshold into the log so subsequent regressions (or unexpected
    pool reclamations) flag themselves at boot.

Behavioural change
------------------

The "ready" log line now branches on IS_ERR_VALUE(pcd->muram_offset):

  SKIP path (default after 0062):
    fman_pcd: ready (MURAM pre-reservation SKIPPED - per PR14z21; \
              per-flow allocs use the full gen_pool)

  RESERVED path (kept for future re-enablement / out-of-tree forks):
    fman_pcd: ready (%u KiB MURAM reserved at offset 0x%lx)

The CP-postinstall line now appends a v1.4 §16 Risk #13 verdict tag
when avail drops below 80 KiB (= ~20% of the 384 KiB LS1046A pool):

  fman_pcd: install_now: muram pool size=393216 B avail=70400 B \
            (post boot-time PCD install) [VERDICT: hypothesis-(a) \
            POOL-ALREADY-TIGHT - boot-time CC trees consumed >=80% \
            of MURAM; per-flow chain_create will be at risk]

If avail >= 80 KiB the tag becomes "[budget-OK]" so a clean run is
also self-documenting.

Diagnostic-only.  No fast-path overhead (both sites are one-shot at
fman_pcd_init() / fman_pcd_install_now_for_existing_ports() epilogue).
---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c
index e4fcc5e..b2f4821 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c
@@ -497,14 +497,31 @@ int fman_pcd_install_now_for_existing_ports(struct fman_pcd *pcd)
 		 * whether boot-time CC trees alone exhaust the pool, or
 		 * whether the residual -ENOMEM is per-flow chain churn.
 		 */
-		struct muram_info *m = fman_get_muram(pcd->fman);
-		size_t ps = 0, pa = 0;
-
-		fman_muram_pool_stats(m, &ps, &pa);
-		dev_info(fman_get_dev(pcd->fman),
-			 "fman_pcd: install_now: muram pool size=%zu B avail=%zu B (post boot-time PCD install)\n",
-			 ps, pa);
-	}
+struct muram_info *m = fman_get_muram(pcd->fman);
+size_t ps = 0, pa = 0;
+const char *verdict;
+/*
+ * v1.4 Phase 5 diagnostic (PR14z23, 2026-05-25): bake the
+ * v1.4 §16 Risk #13 hypothesis-(a) verdict threshold into
+ * the log so subsequent regressions (or unexpected pool
+ * reclamations) flag themselves at boot.  Threshold (80 KiB
+ * = ~20% of the LS1046A 384 KiB pool) matches 0063's
+ * "Hypothesis (a) CONFIRMED if CP-postinstall avail <
+ * ~80 KiB" verdict criterion.
+ */
+#define FMAN_PCD_POSTINSTALL_BUDGET_WARN_BYTES (80U * 1024U)
+
+fman_muram_pool_stats(m, &ps, &pa);
+if (pa < FMAN_PCD_POSTINSTALL_BUDGET_WARN_BYTES)
+verdict = " [VERDICT: hypothesis-(a) POOL-ALREADY-TIGHT - "
+  "boot-time CC trees consumed >=80% of MURAM; "
+  "per-flow chain_create will be at risk]";
+else
+verdict = " [budget-OK]";
+dev_info(fman_get_dev(pcd->fman),
+ "fman_pcd: install_now: muram pool size=%zu B avail=%zu B (post boot-time PCD install)%s\n",
+ ps, pa, verdict);
+}
 	
 	return first_err;
 }
@@ -594,12 +611,22 @@ struct fman_pcd *fman_pcd_init(struct fman *fman)
 					    &fman_pcd_muram_budget_fops);
 	}
 
-	dev_info(fman_get_dev(fman),
-		 "fman_pcd: ready (%u KiB MURAM reserved at offset 0x%lx)\n",
-		 FMAN_PCD_MURAM_RESERVED_BYTES / 1024U,
-		 pcd->muram_offset);
-
-	return pcd;
+/*
+ * v1.4 Phase 5 fix (PR14z23, 2026-05-25): branch on the -EINVAL
+ * sentinel set by PR14z21 (patch 0062) so the SKIP path doesn't
+ * print a misleading "64 KiB reserved at 0xffff...ea" line that
+ * looks like a real reservation at a bogus address.
+ */
+if (IS_ERR_VALUE(pcd->muram_offset))
+dev_info(fman_get_dev(fman),
+ "fman_pcd: ready (MURAM pre-reservation SKIPPED - per PR14z21; per-flow allocs use the full gen_pool)\n");
+else
+dev_info(fman_get_dev(fman),
+ "fman_pcd: ready (%u KiB MURAM reserved at offset 0x%lx)\n",
+ FMAN_PCD_MURAM_RESERVED_BYTES / 1024U,
+ pcd->muram_offset);
+
+return pcd;
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_pcd_init);
 
